Quote: BREMNER Woolscours of NZ 69 To Yorkshireman George Rhodes, sheepfarmer of 'The Levels' in the 1850s, a creek was a 'dyke' and in the creek north of the future city of Timaru he washed his sheep before shearing, and the Washdyke it became. [wash dike]
